cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the limitations of Shannon information measures in accurately determining multivariate dependencies, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the combination of complex network theory with information theory, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
